stories.description:
CONTEXT: The synthesize_node currently concatenates augmented chunks in retrieval order. For long documents with many matching chunks, this wastes the context window with redundant text (chunks from the same section repeat the same ideas). This story adds a pure context packer that groups chunks by section, deduplicates near-duplicate content, and respects a strict token budget. Per Core Belief #19, this is a pure function with no I/O. PURE FUNCTION — Create app/services/context_packer.py. Define: pack_context(chunks: list[dict], token_budget: int = 3000, dedup_ratio: float = 0.8) -> str. The `chunks` list contains dicts with keys: text (str), section_id (str | None), section_heading (str | None), section_summary (str | None), relevance_score (float). Algorithm: (1) Group chunks by section_id (chunks with section_id=None form their own group keyed by chunk index). (2) Sort section groups by their highest relevance_score descending. (3) For each section group (most relevant first): (a) If a section_summary is present and not yet included, emit '### {section_heading}
{section_summary}
' (count tokens). (b) For each chunk in the group (sorted by relevance descending): check if this chunk's text is more than dedup_ratio (80%) similar to any already-emitted text. Similarity = len(longest_common_substring(a, b)) / max(len(a), len(b)). If similar, skip it. Otherwise emit '---
{chunk_text}
'. (c) Stop adding chunks when cumulative token count >= token_budget. (d) Token count estimate: len(text.split()) * 1.3 (fast approximation, no tokenizer dependency). (4) Return the assembled string. EDGE CASES: if chunks is empty, return ''. If all chunks exceed budget individually, include at least the first chunk truncated to token_budget. If dedup_ratio=1.0, deduplication is disabled (always include). INTEGRATION: In synthesize_node in chat_graph.py, replace the ad-hoc chunk concatenation with a call to pack_context(state.chunks, token_budget=3000). The state.section_context (graph results, library summary) is prepended to the pack_context output, capped at 1000 tokens. TESTS — tests/test_context_packer.py: all tests are pure unit tests with no DB or mock setup. (a) test_sections_ordered_by_relevance: chunks from section B have higher score than section A, assert B appears first in output. (b) test_deduplication_skips_similar_chunks: two chunks with > 80% overlap, assert only one appears in output. (c) test_token_budget_enforced: chunks totaling 6000 tokens with budget=3000, assert output token estimate <= 3300 (10% tolerance). (d) test_section_summary_emitted_once: section with 3 chunks and a section_summary, assert section_summary appears exactly once in output. (e) test_empty_chunks_returns_empty_string. (f) test_no_section_id_chunks_handled: all chunks have section_id=None, assert output is non-empty and no exception raised. (g) test_dedup_ratio_1_includes_all: with dedup_ratio=1.0, all chunks within budget are included even if near-duplicate. SMOKE — scripts/smoke/S79.sh: POST /qa with question='What happens in book 1?' for a book document. Assert HTTP 200, answer non-empty, response time < 15 seconds. Exit 0.
